</br>2 He will not cry out or raise [his voice], and in the street he will not let his voice be heard.
</br>3 No crushed reed will he break; and as for a dim flaxen wick, he will not extinguish it. In trueness he will bring forth justice.
</br>4 He will not grow dim nor be crushed until he sets justice in the earth itself; and for his law the islands themselves will keep waiting.
<p></p>
